Checkscripts for Sun Solaris. 

Scripts are Nagios compliant.


check_disk_usage.pl: Checks the used size of a mounted disk device by using UNIX 'df'

	Usage: ./check_disk_usage.pl -f <Mountpoint> -c <Critical size MB> -w <Warning size MB> [-p]
		-p: Include performance data to the output


check_solaris_swap.pl: Checks the used swap space

	Usage: ./check_solaris_swap.pl -c <1-100> -w <1-100> [-p]
		-p: Include performance data to the output
